## Background

From PR #314 code review finding: Log allocations occur even when debug logging is disabled because map parameters are allocated before LogDebug is called.

## Suggested Solution

Add an `IsDebugEnabled()` method to the Logger interface to guard allocations:

```go
if logger.IsDebugEnabled() {
    logger.LogDebug(ctx, "message", map[string]interface{}{
        "expensive": computeValue(),
    })
}
```

Or use a closure-based approach to defer evaluation:

```go
logger.LogDebugLazy(ctx, "message", func() map[string]interface{} {
    return map[string]interface{}{"expensive": computeValue()}
})
```

## Affected Files

- internal/usecase/review/verification.go (logVerificationDetails)
- Potentially other debug logging call sites

## Labels

performance, enhancement
